[normal].However much of the evidence base for these complex relationships between disability and poverty remain ill-defined and under-researched.  Groce et al conducted a review employing systematic methods (though not a systematic review) of peer-reviewed literature of disability and poverty. Of 293 articles identified in the search, only 27 (9.3%) were found to be evidence-based.  
